# FeatBit Deployment Configuration
#
# Copy this file to deployment.env and fill in your values.
# deployment.env is listed in .gitignore so credentials stay off disk.
#
# All values are optional — anything left blank falls back to the script default.
# Pass individual parameters on the command line to override specific values:
#
#   .\Deploy-FeatBitClusters.ps1 -WestCpus 6
#
# ─── Registry ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This project uses three distinct registries.  Understanding which one handles
# which image avoids the most common source of "ImagePullBackOff" failures.
#
# 1. HOST LOCAL REGISTRY  (localhost:5000  /  host.minikube.internal:5000)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A plain registry:2 container running on your developer machine.  It holds only
# the FeatBit application images that are built from source in this repo:
#
#   featbit/api-server
#   featbit/evaluation-server
#   featbit/control-plane
#   featbit/da-server          (data-analytics)
#   featbit/ui
#
# Before deploying you must build each image, tag it, and push it here:
#
#   docker build -t localhost:5000/featbit/api-server:latest ./modules/back-end
#   docker push localhost:5000/featbit/api-server:latest
#
# Inside Minikube the host machine is reachable as host.minikube.internal, so
# the same images are pulled by the cluster using that hostname.  Both clusters
# are started with --insecure-registry=host.minikube.internal:5000, which allows
# HTTP (no TLS) pulls.
#
# Set FEATBIT_IMAGE_REGISTRY only when you have pushed the FeatBit images to a
# different registry (e.g. a shared Harbor, Nexux project).  Leave it blank to use the
# host local registry at host.minikube.internal:5000 (the default).
#
# FEATBIT_IMAGE_REGISTRY=nexus.example.com/featbit
#
#
# 2. CORPORATE / PRIVATE REGISTRY  (CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Holds third-party infrastructure images sourced from Docker Hub:
#
#   mongo, redis, bitnami/kafka, clickhouse/clickhouse-server,
#   ghcr.io/provectus/kafka-ui, etc.
#
# These images are mirrored into the corporate registry to avoid Docker Hub rate
# limits and to keep cluster egress inside the network.  When CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY
# is set, every infrastructure YAML is rewritten at deploy time (via
# extras/Set-InfraImages.ps1 / Invoke-KubectlApplyFile) so image refs point here.
# Leave CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY blank to pull directly from Docker Hub.
#
# CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY=myregistry.example.com
# CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY=myregistry.example.com:5000
#
# TLS trust: if CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY is signed by a CA that is not in the
# public trust store, the recommended path is to configure TRUST_CERTIFICATES
# (see the "Certificate Trust" section near the end of this file).
# Deploy-FeatBitClusters.ps1 will automatically install the trust into each
# Minikube node during cluster bring-up when both CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY and
# TRUST_CERTIFICATES are set.

# Full registry path used to compute the MongoDB and PostgreSQL image references
# passed directly to `kubectl set image`. These calls bypass the image map, so
# this variable must be set explicitly whenever your proxy path does not follow
# the default /dockerhub/library convention.
#
# Default (when omitted): CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY/dockerhub/library
#
# Example — Nexus proxy:
#   CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY=registry.example.com/repository/docker-proxy
#   INFRA_IMAGE_REPOSITORY=registry.example.com/repository/docker-proxy
#     → mongo:7.0  becomes  registry.example.com/repository/docker-proxy/mongo:7.0
#
# Example — Harbor with library prefix:
#   CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY=harbor.example.com
#   INFRA_IMAGE_REPOSITORY=harbor.example.com/dockerhub/library
#
# INFRA_IMAGE_REPOSITORY=myregistry.example.com/mirror/library

# Path to the JSON file that maps Docker Hub image names to registry paths.
# Defaults to kubernetes/infra-image-map.json relative to the repo root.
# For registries with non-standard namespacing (e.g. Harbor), create
# kubernetes/infra-image-map.local.json (gitignored) with your registry paths
# and it will be merged automatically — no need to set this variable.
#
# INFRA_IMAGE_MAP_FILE=

# Credentials for CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY. When both are set, the script creates
# a docker-registry image pull secret in each cluster namespace automatically.
# Leave blank if your registry does not require authentication.
#
# CUSTOM_REGISTRY_USERNAME=myuser
# CUSTOM_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=mypassword

# Secret name created in each cluster namespace to hold the pull credentials.
# Defaults to registry-credentials.
#
# CUSTOM_REGISTRY_SECRET_NAME=registry-credentials

# Set to true to pass --insecure-registry=$CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY to
# minikube start, which disables TLS verification for that host.  Use
# this only when (a) you cannot install a CA, or (b) the registry is
# HTTP-only.  Default is false — proper TLS trust via TRUST_CERTIFICATES
# is preferred.
#
# INSECURE_CUSTOM_REGISTRY=true

# ─── Images ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Override individual infra image references (full image:tag, including registry).
# Leave blank to compute automatically from CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY / INFRA_IMAGE_REPOSITORY.
#
# MONGO_IMAGE=myregistry.example.com/library/mongo:7.0
# POSTGRES_IMAGE=myregistry.example.com/library/postgres:15.10

# Custom Minikube base image as a full image reference.
# Include registry/repository/tag when needed. Leave blank to use the Minikube default.
#
# MINIKUBE_BASE_IMAGE=myregistry.example.com/minikube/kicbase:v0.0.50-corpca

# ─── Deployment ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# DeploymentMode: Basic (default) or Advanced.
#   Basic   — selected infra components run on host Docker; apps deploy to clusters.
#   Advanced — all infra runs inside both clusters.
#
# DEPLOYMENT_MODE=Basic

# DatabaseProvider: MongoDb (default) or Postgres.
#
# DATABASE_PROVIDER=MongoDb

# Comma-separated list of infra components to run on host Docker (Basic mode only).
# Valid values: redis, kafka, clickhouse, mongodb, postgresql
#
# HOST_INFRA_COMPONENTS=redis,kafka,clickhouse,mongodb

# ─── Cluster Resources ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# WEST_CPUS=4
# WEST_MEMORY=8192
# EAST_CPUS=4
# EAST_MEMORY=8192

# ─── Cross-DC Consistency (gated commit) ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# Controls the control-plane gated-commit consistency mode (see
# 00-Docs/GATED-COMMIT-CONSISTENCY.md). Default BestEffort = unchanged behavior.
# Set to GatedCommit to enable: a flag/segment change is not served by any live
# DC until every live DC has it. When GatedCommit, the deploy additionally labels
# each control-plane Redis instance with its DcId and sets each eval server's
# ControlPlane__DcId to match (the cluster name "west"/"east" is used as the DcId).
#
# CONSISTENCY_MODE=BestEffort

# ─── Certificate Trust ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Semicolon-separated list of corporate certificates to trust inside each
# Minikube cluster. Each entry contains three pipe-separated fields:
#   name   — short identifier used for temp-file naming
#   url    — HTTPS URL to download the PEM file from
#   target — absolute path inside the VM where the .crt file is installed
#
# When both CUSTOM_IMAGE_REGISTRY and TRUST_CERTIFICATES are set,
# Deploy-FeatBitClusters.ps1 automatically invokes the trust-installer
# script during cluster bring-up — no separate manual step is needed.
# The installer covers two trust scopes inside each Minikube node:
#   • OS CA store   — so kubectl, curl, and system tools trust the cert.
#   • Docker daemon — /etc/docker/certs.d/<registry-host>/ca.crt, so
#                     image pulls also trust the registry certificate.
#
# Leave blank (or omit) to use the built-in defaults.
#
# Example:
#   TRUST_CERTIFICATES=my-corp-ca|https://certs.example.com/ca.pem|/usr/local/share/ca-certificates/my-corp-ca.crt
#
# TRUST_CERTIFICATES=
